09/08/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Saudi Arabia's King Abdullah, accompanied by a large delegation of government officials and businessmen, kicked off a three-day formal visit to Turkey on Tuesday (8 August). 
This is the first such visit by a Saudi monarch. 
Representatives of both countries expect it to result in the launching of a strategic bilateral partnership and intensified economic ties. 
On Tuesday, a total of six agreements were sealed, on topics ranging from healthcare to investments. 
(Zaman - 09/08/06; Anadolu Agency, NTV - 08/08/06)
